{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"beb326d2-5f6f-4a27-b309-c73d091c6551","content":"Here's the correct skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute | Example |\n|-----------|-----------|---------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` | `[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` | `[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` | `[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` | `[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]` |\n\n**Notes:**\n- For xUnit `[Theory]` tests, it's the same pattern: `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]`.\n- MSTest and NUnit both use `[Ignore]` but they come from different namespaces (`Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` vs `NUnit.Framework`).\n- All four frameworks support a reason string, which is recommended so teammates know *why* a test is skipped.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5726ad36-d20c-427d-a8f7-06402a239fa8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct skip/ignore attributes for each test framework. I have a skill that could help with this - the `dotnet-test-frameworks` skill which contains reference data for test framework detection patterns, assertion APIs, skip annotations, etc.","outputTokens":329,"requestId":"981A:180764:1AB6B4:22FA8D:69FFDC0D"},"id":"4cc6ebf9-c8ee-4347-b19f-578f8f245a68","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:15:01.234Z","parentId":"dfa1bcc9-1083-4cc1-b193-6fdc150e7113"}
